        "score": 0.6075718,
        "text": "The document page is from Section 7: Congestion Revenue Rights of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, dated February 1, 2025. It lists various energy sources and their associated costs or formulas for calculating costs in $/MWh. The sources include Hydro, Coal and Lignite, Combined Cycle, Gas-Steam Boilers, Simple Cycle, Diesel, Wind, Photovoltaic (PV), and Reliability Must-Run (RMR) Resources. Specific formulas involve the Fuel Index Price (FIP) and MMBtu/MWh multipliers for different types of energy generation. \n\nTwo placeholders, labeled NPRR1188 and NPRR1014, suggest future system implementations with specified costs for CLR and ESR. The page also defines variables MINRESPRi and MINRESPRPj, which represent the minimum resource prices for sources and resources at specific settlement points.",
        "metadata": {
