        "score": 0.6027405,
        "text": "The document page is from Section 9: Settlement and Billing of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, dated February 1, 2025. It lists various sections related to payments and charges within the energy market. These include:\n\n- MRA (Market Resource Adequacy) payments and charges for capital expenditures, deployment events, variable payments, unexcused misconduct, and service charges.\n- Voltage support service payments and charges.\n- Black start services, including hourly standby fee and capacity charges.\n- Payments for emergency operations and real-time revenue neutrality allocation.\n- Emergency response service capacity payments and charges.\n- Firm fuel supply service payments, including hourly standby fee and capacity charges.\n- Real-time settlement for updated day-ahead market ancillary service obligations.\n- Regulation up and down service payments and charges.\n- Responsive reserve payments and charges.\n- Non-spinning reserve service payments and charges.\n- ERCOT contingency reserve service payments and charges.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_9:_Settlement_and_Billing/page_17.jpg",
