      },
      {
        "id": "faeaeebc-4ed5-49ff-bc2f-ab1fb15f76b5",
        "score": 0.59205824,
        "text": "The document page outlines procedures related to Securitization Uplift Charges in the context of electricity market operations. Key points include:\n\n1. **Opt-Out Entities**: Transmission-voltage customers of a REP (Retail Electric Provider) who opt out will have specific ESI IDs included in the Adjusted Metered Load (AML) adjustments. These are based on notifications filed by a deadline in a specific PUCT project.\n\n2. **Return of Securitization Proceeds**: If a Load-Serving Entity (LSE) is required to return securitization proceeds, it must remit these to its Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) within two business days. The QSE then sends the funds to ERCOT for payment of Securitization Uplift Charge Invoices.\n\n3. **Securitization Uplift Charge Calculation**: ERCOT allocates charges to QSEs representing LSEs. The charge for each QSE on an operating day is calculated using a formula involving several variables, such as DQSELERS and DERCOTQSELERS. Definitions for these variables are provided, including LASUCAMT, which represents the charge allocated to each QSE.\n\nThe document is part of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, effective October 1, 2024.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/protocol/ERCOT_Nodal_Protocols:_Section_27:_Securitization_Uplift_Charges/page_4.jpg",
          "page_num": 4,
          "title": "ERCOT Nodal Protocols: Section 27: Securitization Uplift Charges",
          "year": "",
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "protocol"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "eb00e36e-1580-465c-859c-c6c0206e4415",
        "score": 0.58834755,
        "text": "The document page is from Section 26: Securitization Default Charges of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, dated December 1, 2024. It provides definitions and explanations related to securitization default charges for market participants. Key terms include:\n\n- **OBLP**: Represents the MW quantity for PTP Obligation Purchase per Market Participant per source and sink pair per CRR Auction per hour.\n- **SDCOBLP**: Represents the monthly total MW quantity for PTP Obligation bids in CRR Auctions.\n- **SDCWSLTOT**: Represents the monthly sum of Wholesale Storage Load metered energy for Market Participants.\n- **MEBL**: Represents the metered energy for Wholesale Storage Load at a bus.\n\nAdditional terms define various parameters like counter-parties, settlement points, and intervals.\n\nThe document outlines the allocation of the Securitization Default Charge amount based on the pro-rata share of MWhs contributed by QSE or CRR Account Holders. It also describes the annual evaluation by ERCOT to determine if the Total Securitization Default Charge Monthly Amount (TSDCMA) needs modification. ERCOT will notify Market Participants of any changes at least 15 days in advance.",
