s needed to \nconnect a generator to a new or existing substation on the ERCOT Transmission Grid. These details include \nconceptual design descriptions, construction milestones, and cost estimates. \n– If the costs of the Transmission Facilities are expected to exceed $25,000,000, ERCOT shall perform an \nEconomic Study. This study helps determine the annual production cost saving and annual generator revenue \nreduction resulting from the project addition.\n31\nPUBLIC FIS Report and Follow-up\n• Once studies are approved, ERCOT will notify the TSP and the IE when each study element report is \nposted. The TSP shall provide a copy of each final report to the IE upon request."
