        "score": 0.55552185,
        "text": "The document outlines the process for determining the Securitization Uplift Charge Credit Exposure for a Counter-Party as per ERCOT protocols. It includes:\n\n1. **Conditions for Insufficient Payments**: \n   - Insufficient payments of Securitization Default Charge Invoices.\n   - Requests for Securitization Default Charge Escrow Deposits.\n\n2. **Calculation of Credit Exposure**:\n   - For each Counter-Party, ERCOT calculates the Securitization Uplift Charge Credit Exposure using a formula involving several variables.\n   - The formula considers the maximum of CPMQSELSELRS and CPIEMLSELRS over a specified period, adjusted by the MTSUCDA factor.\n\n3. **Definitions of Variables**:\n   - **LASUCCE_cp**: Represents the estimated forward exposure for unbilled Securitization Uplift Charge Initial Invoices.\n   - **CPMQSELSELRS_cp,om,las**: Counter-Party Monthly QSE Non-Opted-Out LSE Load Ratio Share.\n   - **CPIEMLSELRS_cp**: Calculated using CPIEMLSE and MERCOTQSELSETARML.\n   - **MQSELSELRS**: Ratio of MQSELSETARML to MERCOTQSELSETARML.\n   - **MQSELSETARML**: Sum of DQSELSETARML over all days.\n   - **MERCOTQSELSETARML**: Sum of DQSELSETARML for all QSEs.\n\nThe document provides a detailed mathematical framework for calculating financial exposure related to securitization uplift charges.",
