        "score": 0.5479004,
        "text": "The document page is from Section 5: Transmission Security Analysis and Reliability Unit Commitment of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, dated February 1, 2025. It details startup and operational costs for various power generation configurations.\n\n1. **Startup Costs**:\n   - **Simple Cycle \u2265 90 MW**: $5,000 for cold, intermediate, and hot startups.\n   - **Combined Cycle**: Costs are the sum of individual unit costs within the configuration.\n     - Combustion turbine < 90 MW: $2,300 for all startup types.\n     - Combustion turbine \u2265 90 MW: $5,000 for all startup types.\n     - Steam turbine: Costs decrease from $3,000 (cold) to $1,250 (hot).\n     - Gas-steam non-reheat boiler: Costs decrease from $2,310 (cold) to $866.25 (hot).\n     - Gas-steam reheat boiler: Costs decrease from $3,000 (cold) to $1,125 (hot).\n     - Gas-steam supercritical boiler: Costs decrease from $4,800 (cold) to $1,800 (hot).\n     - Nuclear, coal, lignite, and hydro: Costs decrease from $7,200 (cold) to $2,700 (hot).\n     - Renewable: Not applicable.\n\n2. **Variable O&M Costs**:\n   - Simple cycle \u2265 90 MW: $3.94/MWh.\n   - Combined cycle: $3.19/MWh.\n   - Gas-steam non-reheat, reheat, and supercritical boilers: $7.08/MWh.\n   - Nuclear, coal, lignite, and hydro: $5.02/MWh.\n   - Renewable: $5.50/MWh.\n\n3. **O&M Cost Reduction**:\n   - For 2012, standard O&M costs are reduced by 10% from the specified levels.\n\n4. **Resource Category Costs for 2009**:\n   - Aeroderivative simple cycle: $900 for all startup types, $3.55/MWh for variable O&M.\n   - Reciprocating Engine: $52.20/MW based on seasonal net max sustainable ratings, $4.58/MWh for variable O&M.\n   - Simple cycle < 90 MW: $2,070 for all startup types, $3.55/MWh for variable O&M.\n   - Simple cycle \u2265 90 MW: $4,500 for all startup types, $3.55/MWh for variable O&M.\n   - Combined cycle: Costs vary by unit type within the configuration.\n   - Gas-steam non-reheat and reheat boilers: Costs decrease from $2,079 (cold) to $779.63 (hot), $6.37/MWh for variable O&M.",
