        "text": "The document outlines financial security requirements for Market Participants in the ERCOT region, focusing on enforcement levels and the release of financial security.\n\n1. **Financial Security Increase**: \n   - Market Participants must increase their financial security to at least 110% of their Total Potential Exposure (TPE) or any other liability to ERCOT within two Bank Business Days if they have already provided financial security.\n\n2. **Duration of Requirements**:\n   - Increased financial security requirements remain for a minimum of 60 days and continue until ERCOT decides to reduce them.\n\n3. **Level II Enforcement**:\n   - ERCOT will notify Market Participants to provide financial security at 115% of their TPE or other liabilities within two Bank Business Days. This requirement also lasts for a minimum of 60 days.\n\n4. **Level III Enforcement**:\n   - ERCOT will require financial security at 120% of TPE within two Bank Business Days, with excess security in the form of a cash deposit. This requirement lasts for a minimum of 90 days.\n\n5. **Release of Financial Security**:\n   - After terminating a Standard Form Market Participant Agreement, ERCOT retains financial security to cover potential future obligations.",
